    * *     [Fashion.] The number of times you have seen them crash into one of the food stalls, or even worse the time they mistook those slime skates for their own, beg to differ.
    
        You do not labor under the misapprehension that their pants magically rearrange their (precisely cut) holes.
        
        Indeed, Plume is possessed of a rather refined taste in delinquent couture.
        
    * *     (trains) [Trains.] When, reluctantly, they brought you by their student housing in the neighborhood for hauling back some hand-crafted committee bits and bobs, you saw something.
    
        You did not at all mean to be nosy. The basement window was ajar, the air around it saturated with inexplicable mechanical whirring.
        
        What you saw changed your view of Plume forever.
        
        * * *   Trains.[] Miles and miles of--to scale, faithfully reproduced--tracks and trains of disgustingly decadent variety.
        
            A scale model of what you believe to be the valley they hail from, the high walls of Granbury rising into view at the western edge.
        
            Out of concern for your safety, honey, I ask that you contradict their modeling argument with something less crippling to their already fragile ego.
