*   [Plume doesn't deserve this] Even in this obnoxiously idealized, saccharine world, incarceration is an absolute nightmare complex of human rights abuses.

    Plume may not be human, but they do have rights, as far as you're concerned.
    
    They are the furthest thing from a model citizen, but nobody deserves to be caged on a beautiful Spring day like today. 
    
    -> modeling
-
    The real argument to be had, of course, is that this mode of imprisonment is far crueler and far far more unusual than anything else the Headmaster has subjected them to today.
    
    Truly, a bird should not be caged. No bird especially should ever be caged in a cardboard box with paper towel roll bars.
    
    p pissed: They're not--
    
    Plume hesitantly taps the bars with an aglet from one of their skates.
    
    They are rewarded with the dull report identifying the material with paper towel rolls, albeit ones carefully painted to kind-of sort-of look like steel bars.
    
    p: Oh my god.
    
    b aura: Rock solid defense. Genius lady. Miss Headmaster can't be beat. 
    
    b frown_sweating: Yous up a creek, kid.
    
